Why AGPL-3.0?

The kyber-platform runs as a network service (HTTPS). Standard GPL allows
modified versions to be run as a service without releasing source changes.
The AGPL closes this loophole: if you deploy a modified version of this
platform — even over a network — you must make the complete modified source
code available to users of that service under the same license.

This ensures that improvements to the educational platform remain open and
available to the community.

---

Additional Terms — Scope of the License

This license applies to:

  - The FastAPI backend (auth.py, challenges.py, leaderboard.py,
    answer_validator.py, challenge_store.py, rate_limit.py, security.py)
  - The NGINX configuration (nginx.conf, app.conf)
  - The Docker orchestration (docker-compose.yml, Dockerfile)
  - The database schema (01_schema.sql)
  - The static frontend (index.html, login.html, main.html)
  - All shell scripts (start.sh, stop.sh, backup.sh,
    enable_tls.sh, disable_tls.sh)

The cryptographic challenge content (questions, worked examples, and
answer keys) is NOT covered by this license. All challenge content is
© 2026 Georgios Efthymiou — All Rights Reserved. You may not reproduce,
distribute, or create derivative works from the challenge content without
explicit written permission.

